7054322/https://www.charlotteobserver.com/news/local/article241209266.html |archive-date=March 17, 2020 }}</ref>\n* North Dakota: Governor Burgum ordered all schools to be closed from March 16 to March 20. It was confirmed the state lab had tested 112 individuals for the virus with one case coming back positive from a person with travel history.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.governor.nd.gov/news/burgum-orders-k-12-schools-close-one-week-effort-slow-spread-covid-19 |title=Burgum orders K-12 schools to close for one week in effort to slow spread of COVID-19 |date=March 15, 2020 |website=North Dakota Office of the Governor |language=en |access-date=March 18, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318065016/https://www.governor.nd.gov/news/burgum-orders-k-12-schools-close-one-week-effort-slow-spread-covid-19 |archive-date=March 18, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> \n* New York: New York City mayor DeBlasio announced that New York public schools, the largest public school system in the country, would be closed starting Monday, March 16.  The closure will last at least through April 20.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://nypost.com/2020/03/15/coronavirus-in-ny-nyc-schools-will-close/ |title=Coronavirus in NY: NYC schools will close |date=15 March 2020 |website=New York Post |url-status=live |access-date=16 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200316223748/https://nypost.com/2020/03/15/coronavirus-in-ny-nyc-schools-will-close/ |archive-date=March 16, 2020 }}</ref>\n* Ohio: Governor DeWine orders all bars and restaurants to close beginning at 9:00 PM. Establishments may continue providing take-out and delivery services.<ref name=\"ILLINOIS OHIO THE HILL RESTAURANTS\" />\n* Oklahoma: [[Kevin Stitt|Governor Stitt]] declared a state-wide state of emergency. The state reported its eighth case of coronavirus.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://oklahoman.com/article/5657708/coronavirus-in-oklahoma-stitt-declares-state-of-emergency/ |title=Coronavirus in Oklahoma: S