r the [[2020 Illinois Democratic primary]] was low, but Chicago broke a World War II-era record for mail-in voting.<ref>[https://www.chicagotribune.com/election-2020/ct-illinois-primary-election-day-updates-20200317-gf5morm2gzbc5j3laniwpr5kx4-story.html Illinois primary updates: Polls about to close after \u2018extremely low\u2019 turnout in Chicago amid coronavirus turmoil] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318032402/https://www.chicagotribune.com/election-2020/ct-illinois-primary-election-day-updates-20200317-gf5morm2gzbc5j3laniwpr5kx4-story.html |date=March 18, 2020 }} Chicago Tribune, 17 Mar 2020</ref>\n*Maryland: Maryland postponed all state primaries until June 2 to reduce the risk of coronavirus infection to the Marylanders.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.politico.com/news/2020/03/17/maryland-postpones-april-28-primary-election-over-coronavirus-133776|title=Maryland postpones primary, shifts special election to mail voting over coronavirus|website=POLITICO|language=en|access-date=2020-03-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318104700/https://www.politico.com/news/2020/03/17/maryland-postpones-april-28-primary-election-over-coronavirus-133776|archive-date=March 18, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*Minnesota: The Minnesota Department of Health announced that due to the national shortage of materials for medical testing for the virus they will be limiting testing to those who are hospitalized, ill healthcare workers and those who live in long-term care facilities. The restrictions will be in place until the state is supplied with additional tests.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fox9.com/news/minnesota-dept-of-health-narrowing-testing-criteria-amid-national-shortage-of-covid-19-tests|title=Minnesota Dept. of Health narrowing testing criteria amid national shortage of COVID-19 tests|accessdate=March 24, 2020}}</ref>\n*North Carolina: The state announced that it had 65 confirmed coronavirus cases.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.newsobserve