6/coronavirus-live-updates-us-death-toll-rises-cases-testing/5053816002/ Coronavirus live updates: Guidelines call for no groups bigger than 10; Trump says restrictions could last into August] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318042652/https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/health/2020/03/16/coronavirus-live-updates-us-death-toll-rises-cases-testing/5053816002/ |date=March 18, 2020 }} by John Bacon & Jorge L. Ortiz, USA Today, 16 Mar 2020</ref>\n* Colorado: Colorado announced 29 new positive cases of COVID-19, bringing the state total to 160.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.cpr.org/2020/03/16/polis-considering-statewide-closure-of-bars-restaurants-gyms-and-theaters/ |title=Polis Orders Statewide Closure of Seating at Bars, Restaurants |last=Markus |first=Ben |website=Colorado Public Radio |access-date=2020-03-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318041907/https://www.cpr.org/2020/03/16/polis-considering-statewide-closure-of-bars-restaurants-gyms-and-theaters/ |archive-date=March 18, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Michael Hancock (Colorado politician)|Mayor Hancock]] of [[Denver]] orders all bars and restaurants close by 8AM, March 17 (excepting food delivery and pickup) and also bans gatherings of more than 50 people in the city.<ref name=\"CO_mar16\">{{Cite news |last=Oravetz |first=Janet |url=https://www.9news.com/article/news/health/coronavirus/denver-coronavirus-update/73-e04fa1e5-bf55-443a-83ed-6fb3e9d02dcc |title=All Denver restaurants and bars ordered to close to indoor dining for 8 weeks |access-date=16 March 2020 |publisher=NBC - 9News}}</ref> [[Jared Polis|Governor Polis]] expanded the closures by ordering a state-wide closure of dine-in services. Polis also ordered the closure of gyms, casinos, and theaters.<ref name=\"CO_mar16_polis\">{{Cite news |last=Wingerter |first=Meg |url=https://www.denverpost.com/2020/03/16/coronavirus-colorado-bars-restaurants-dmv-closed/ |title=Colorado governor orders bars, restaurants to halt dine-